## DMS-NAS Cursor Rules (Master v2)

### Goal
Construction Company DMS: Telegram Bot + Django Web Admin.
Files on Synology NAS (DSM File Station API). Metadata in SQLite (→ Postgres later).
See full spec: docs/MASTER_SPEC.md

### Synology API — NON-NEGOTIABLE
- Base: https://stroydnepr.synology.me:5001/webapi/entry.cgi
- Pass _sid and SynoToken in query string on EVERY request.
- Use LOGICAL paths (/Днепр, /Обмен) — NEVER /volume1/...
- Upload: multipart/form-data POST; tokens ONLY in URL query string, NOT in form body.
- Support Cyrillic paths and filenames (UTF-8).
- All NAS ops retry 1–3 times with backoff.

### Architecture — NON-NEGOTIABLE
- Do NOT duplicate logic between bot and web.
- Business logic ONLY in core/services/*.
- NAS access ONLY via core/nas_client.py.
- DB mutations via bot_db.py or core/services; keep consistent.
- Monitoring/alerts via core/monitoring.py.

### NAS folder structure (canonical)
/{Object}/
  _INBOX/{Сертификат|ТТН|Акт|Протокол|ФотоОтчет|Другое}/
  _APPROVED/{same}/
  _REJECTED/{same}/
  ФотоОтчет/ | _PACKAGES/ | Финансы/{_INBOX|Счета|ТТН|Акты|Договоры|Прочее|_EXPORTS}/
  Журналы/ | ТБ_ОТ/

### Quality rules
- All approve/reject/status/reminder actions are IDEMPOTENT.
- Wrap multi-step DB updates in transactions where possible.
- Log every NAS op and DB mutation with: user_id, role, object, path, result.
- Preserve ALL acceptance tests (docs/ACCEPTANCE_TESTS.md); add new tests for new features.

### Callback_data (Telegram)
- Max 64 bytes. NEVER put full paths in callback_data.
- Use _pid()/_pget() from bot.py for all NAS path references in keyboards.

### Security
- Telegram: check _has(update, perm) on every handler entry.
- Web: @staff_member_required or group check on every non-public view.
- NAS proxy: server downloads, browser never touches NAS directly.

### Finance transitions (enforced, never bypass)
черновик → на_проверке → утверждён → оплачен
на_проверке → отклонён → черновик

### Sprints status
