- Sprint 10:    Postgres — code ready (migrate_sqlite_to_postgres.py), switch DB_MODE = "postgres"
- Sprint 11:    DONE — documents registry, SHA-256 dedup, doc_id in uploads/finance
- Sprint 12:    DONE — object-level permissions (user_objects, /grant, /revoke, /listaccess)
- Sprint 13:    DONE — mass ops, Web→Telegram notifications, weekly digest
- Sprint 14:    DONE — PDF reports (ReportLab), Excel export (openpyxl), favicon
- Sprint 15:    DONE (MVP) — OCR via pdfplumber + pytesseract, human-in-the-loop web form
- Sprint 14 DR: TODO — docs/DR_RUNBOOK.md + restore scripts
- Sprint 16:    TODO — RAG/semantic search (Qdrant + embeddings)
- Sprint 17:    TODO — 1С/ERP export, SMTP, SSO

### v2 Roadmap constraints (MASTER_SPEC_v2.md)
- Never commit secrets to repo. Use bot_config_local.py in .gitignore or env vars.
- Sprint 10: migrate SQLite -> Postgres with verification and rollback plan.
- Sprint 11: documents registry with doc_id and SHA-256 deduplication. ✅
- Sprint 12: object-level permissions enforced in bot AND web. ✅
- Sprint 13: mass operations + quality dashboard + Web→Telegram notifications. ✅
- Sprint 14: DR runbook + restore scripts + backup verification + PDF/Excel reports. ✅ partial
- Sprint 15+: OCR ONLY via background worker/thread; NEVER in request path. ✅
- Sprint 16: RAG/semantic search via Qdrant, embeddings, "answer with sources".
- Sprint 17: 1С/ERP CSV export, SMTP email, SSO/AD.
- All stages: audit_log every mutation, idempotent operations, retry NAS ops 1-3x.
- Acceptance tests: P-series (Postgres), D-series (Docs), O-series (Objects),
                    M-series (Mass ops), R-series (DR), OCR-series.
- See full spec: docs/MASTER_SPEC_v2.md
